00:00:10,840 --> 00:00:13,910
Hughes-san... I'm here again.

2
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:34,300
For crying out loud,

3
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:38,170
be more thorough when you rebuild these things, would you, Winry?

4
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:46,420
Now what do we do?

5
00:00:46,420 --> 00:00:48,860
There's still a good distance to go 
before we reach Ishbal.

6
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:50,520
What do we do?

7
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:52,000
All we can do is walk.

8
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:57,420
Eh!? We can't! I might be all right, 
but it's going to wear you out, Brother.

9
00:00:57,420 --> 00:00:58,870
Then what would you rather do?!

10
00:00:58,870 --> 00:01:03,460
There aren't any tracks into Ishbal, 
all the usual roads have been closed down,

11
00:01:03,460 --> 00:01:05,970
and we can't very well get the military to send us there anymore.

12
00:01:05,970 --> 00:01:07,320
You <i>are</i> right about that...

13
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:08,810
Let's just keep going.

14
00:01:08,810 --> 00:01:10,840
If we just stand around here,

15
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:13,370
Ishbal isn't very well 
going to come to us.

16
00:01:13,370 --> 00:01:15,490
Brother!

17
00:01:15,490 --> 00:01:18,970
Jeez, why is he always so haphazard?

18
00:01:19,890 --> 00:01:23,780
Man cannot obtain anything 
without first sacrificing something.

19
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:28,370
In order to obtain anything, 
something of equal value is required.

20
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:33,410
That is alchemy's 
Law of Equivalent Exchange.

21
00:01:34,630 --> 00:01:39,490
At the time, we believed that 
to be the true way of the world.

22
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:53,660
Far away, far away, our dreams will never fade

23
